---
Source:
  Title: A Year with Hafiz
  Translator: Daniel Ladinsky
  Author: Hafiz
  ISBN: 978-0143117544
  Publisher: Penguin Books
Format: Verse
By: Hafiz
Title: Still Wrapped
Description: December 22
Glossary:
  - Term: mashuq
    Language: Persian
    Definition: beloved or sweetheart
---
“But I don’t look like a sun,”

a young star still wrapped in swaddling veils said.

To which I replied,

“But you will, my dear. You will, mashuq. So don’t worry. Don’t fret.”
